data.message: I would like to know where my newsfeed ticker is. All my friend categories, messages, events everything disappeared from my home page on the left. I should be able to see it and click on it but there is nothing there. I have sent in a help request but have gotten nothing back please help!!!!!!!!!!!!!

replies.message: Hey Candy. If you don't see ticker, check to see if you've hidden or minimized it. For instructions on how to unhide your ticker, visit our Help Center: http://on.fb.me/1uwaNDF. You may also be able to check the status of your report here: http://on.fb.me/1uwaLLO Hope this helps! -Elissa
I tried checking for it being hidden and it didnt work but I will check again.

I don't have a ticker at all or a place to drag it down from there is nothing there. It is completely blank underneath my name and picture. There are not events, friend categories nothing. It was there one day then gone the next after the time change.
I also checked the status of my report and all it said they said thanks for the feedback and blah blah blah. I want my stuff fixed!!!!!!!!

Candy Layne-Truxton - You don't see your Facebook ticker becos you or someone might have zoomed in the view in your screen.  Try zooming out by pressing your keyboard's Ctrl key and - (minus) key simultaneously or successively.
If you don't like it. Jut leave. Stop complaining,
